{
  "texts": [
    "Another key challenge in the process of graph pooling is to ensure the invariance of the node order.",
    "PATCHY-SAN (Niepert et al. 2016) cleverly transforms the graph structure into a standardized form and applies convolution operations, which not only solves the problem of node order but also enables graph structure data to better adapt to traditional convolution operations.",
    "This pooling method not only improves the performance of graph neural networks but also enhances their accuracy when processing graph data.",
    "SortPool (Zhang et al. 2018a) adopts a strategy of sorting node features, selects the top-k features after sorting as pooled features, and then compresses these features into a fixed-length vector representation.",
    "This pooling method helps convert the structural information of the graph into a sequentialized representation, allowing subsequent traditional sequence models or transformer models to better process graph data."
  ]
}